{"id":4555,"date":"2023-12-08T15:46:20","date_gmt":"2023-12-08T04:46:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/?post_type=help_centre&#038;p=4555"},"modified":"2023-12-08T15:49:07","modified_gmt":"2023-12-08T04:49:07","slug":"motor-vibrations","status":"publish","type":"help_centre","link":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/help-centre\/troubleshooting\/motor-vibrations\/","title":{"rendered":"Motor vibrations\u00a0"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>If you are experiencing vibrations in the motor while using the Stoke Foil Boost, performing a thorough check on specific components is essential.&nbsp;<\/p><ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Examine the propeller blade bolts to ensure they are not loose. If they are, tighten them appropriately. However, it&#8217;s crucial not to over-tighten, as this can lead to other issues.&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n<li>Examine the nut on the motor shaft holding the prop housing. Confirm that this nut is tight. If it&#8217;s loose, carefully tighten.<\/li><\/ul><p>Motor vibrations can sometimes occur due to components&#8217; natural wear and tear. Establish a routine of regular checks on the prop blade bolts and motor shaft nut. This proactive approach can help identify and address potential issues before they escalate.<\/p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What should I do if my battery terminals are exposed to water?<\/h3><p>If your battery terminals are exposed to water, it is crucial to address the situation promptly and with caution:<\/p><ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Carefully and quickly dry the battery terminals and charge plug using a clean, dry cloth. Remove any water droplets to prevent further contact with the electrical components.<\/li>\n\n<li>Assess the extent of water exposure. A few small drops that are dried immediately may not pose a significant risk, but if the battery has been immersed or if there&#8217;s any doubt, take the situation seriously.<\/li>\n\n<li>Keep a close eye on the battery. Monitor for any signs of unusual behaviour, such as overheating, swelling, or a change in colour. If you notice anything unusual, stop using the battery immediately.<\/li>\n\n<li>If there&#8217;s a battery fire risk, isolate the battery by removing it from the device or equipment. Store the battery in a fireproof container, ideally placed outside and away from flammable materials, until a proper assessment can be conducted.<\/li><\/ul><p>Remember, water exposure to battery terminals can lead to serious safety risks, including the potential for a battery fire. It&#8217;s essential to prioritise safety and take appropriate measures to assess and address the situation. If in doubt, contact our team for help.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>If you are experiencing vibrations in the motor while using the Stoke Foil Boost, performing a thorough check on specific components is essential.&nbsp; Motor vibrations can sometimes occur due to components&#8217; natural wear and tear. Establish a routine of regular checks on the prop blade bolts and motor shaft nut. This proactive approach can help [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-4555","help_centre","type-help_centre","status-publish","hentry","help_centre_category-troubleshooting"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/help_centre\/4555","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/help_centre"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/help_centre"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/help_centre\/4555\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":4556,"href":"https:\/\/www.stokefoilin